Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at the Institute of Peace in Washington, D.C. during National Small Business Week. He praised the millions of small businesses that contribute to the American economy and acknowledged the presence of Linda McMahon, Administrator of the Small Business Administration, and Ivanka Trump, who has been a champion for women in business. Pence emphasized President Donald Trump's commitment to supporting small businesses and highlighted the administration's efforts to cut job-killing regulations, pass tax cuts, repeal Obamacare, and invest in infrastructure. He expressed confidence in the future of American small businesses under the leadership of President Trump.